title: News Corp. announces it will cut 1,250 positions this year
description: News Corp, which owns The Wall Street Journal and HarperCollins, said it would cut 1,250 positions in 2023.

title: CNBC Daily Open: The U.S. economy gives conflicting signals
description: U.S. stocks drop as the Treasury yields widen their inversion. The U.S. economy gives conflicting signals.

title: Jeep reveals its most expensive Wrangler SUV ever, topping $115,000
description: The limited-edition vehicle is the 2023 Wrangler Rubicon 392 20th Anniversary with heavy-duty off-road parts customization from American Expedition Vehicles.

title: Lyft shares tank 20% after company issues weak guidance
description: Lyft shares fell more than 20% during after hours trading after issuing weak guidance in its earnings report on Thursday.

title: Angry senators grill Pentagon officials over Chinese spy balloon response
description: Senators were visibly angry as they pressed Pentagon officials on when they learned of the Chinese spy balloon, and why they waited so long to shoot it down.

title: SpaceX successfully test fires Starship booster in last key step before orbital launch
description: SpaceX on Thursday test fired 31 of the 33 engines in the towering rocket booster of its Starship prototype.

title: Iconic Kobe Bryant jersey sells for record $5.8 million at auction
description: The jersey worn by the late basketball star during 25 games of his 2007-2008 season is now the most expensive Kobe Bryant item ever sold at auction.

title: Yahoo to lay off 20% of staff by year-end, beginning this week
description: Yahoo will lay off more than 20% of staff, or around 1,600 workers, with the company's Yahoo for Business being slashed in half, the company said.

title: Donald Trump can access his Facebook and Instagram accounts again
description: Meta previously said it planned to reinstate the Trump's accounts, determining that "the risk has sufficiently receded," since the original ban in early 2021.

title: Biden's billionaire tax is 'dead on arrival' in Congress, top Wall Street backers and Democratic strategists say
description: Biden's billionaire tax would subject households with a net worth above $100 million to pay a minimum annual tax of 20% on gains of their "tradable assets."

title: General Motors signs deal with GlobalFoundries for exclusive U.S. semiconductor production
description: GM has signed a long-term agreement with GlobalFoundries to establish exclusive production capacity of U.S.-produced semiconductor chips.

title: Fast food reigns supreme as inflation weighs on pricier restaurants
description: Fast-casual and full-service restaurants like Chipotle and Chili's are struggling to attract customers.

title: Third Point becomes latest activist investor to take stake in Salesforce
description: Dan Loeb's hedge fund Third Point has built a position in Salesforce, CNBC has confirmed.

title: Tether records surprise profit as stablecoin giant aims to put reserve controversy behind it
description: Tether on Thursday said it generated $700 million of profit in the December quarter, which the firm has used to boost its reserves.

title: Disney CEO Bob Iger says he prefers to stay only two years, calls streaming 'the future'
description: Disney CEO Bob Iger told CNBC he plans to stay only for two years, and that he wants more "Toy Story" and "Frozen" sequels.

title: As demand for Covid vaccines falls, AstraZeneca lines up 'blockbuster' products for 2023
description: Demand for Covid-19 vaccines has dropped, but AstraZeneca has "blockbuster" projects in development that are set to make billions of dollars, according to its CFO.

title: Bank of England Governor Bailey says expected drop in inflation should factor into pay demands
description: Bank of England Governor Andrew Bailey has urged workers and employers to consider the expected sharp fall in inflation this year when negotiating pay settlements.

title: Twitter restored in Turkey after meeting with government officials
description: Twitter was blocked for many Turks for several hours on Wednesday after a series of earthquakes hit Turkey and Syria on Monday.

title: Russian forces are closing in on the strategic city of Bakhmut, giving Ukraine a tough choice to make
description: Russia recently claimed that its forces have almost entirely encircled Bakhmut. Now, Ukraine has to decide how much longer it will try to defend it.

title: Investors sue Shell’s board of directors over climate strategy in a first-of-its-kind lawsuit
description: The case comes shortly after Shell reported its highest-ever annual profit of nearly $40 billion.

title: NYU's 'Dean of Valuation' says Adani Group exploited 'weakest links' in Indian institutions
description: The finance professor at the Stern school of business said fundamentals "never come into play" for Indian markets.

title: Ukraine's Zelenskyy expected to ask for more aid from European leaders in Brussels trip
description: Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskyy will be in Brussels to ask EU lawmakers and leaders for more support as Russia's invasion of Ukraine drags on.

title: These are the best hotels in the U.S. and Europe, according to a new ranking
description: The report, published Tuesday, also ranks hotels in the Caribbean, Mexico, Bermuda and Canada, as well as cities and regions across North America and Europe.

title: Chinese A.I. stocks jump on growing ChatGPT interest, state media warns of risks
description: Growing interest surrounding OpenAI's ChatGPT have led China-listed stocks related to artificial intelligence soaring this year so far.

title: Web browser Opera is planning to incorporate ChatGPT
description: Niche web browser Opera is planning to integrate ChatGPT into its products, Opera's parent Kunlun Tech announced Wednesday.

title: Turkey's devastating earthquake comes at a critical time for the country's future
description: This year is a crucial inflection point for Turkey as it approaches its presidential election on May 14.

title: CNBC Daily Open: The Fed made sure U.S. markets are listening: Interest rates will continue rising
description: After weeks of defying the Federal Reserve, U.S. markets realized that interest rate hikes are probably here to stay.

title: Credit Suisse posts massive annual loss as 'radical' restructure gets underway
description: Credit Suisse on Thursday reported a fourth-quarter net loss of 1.4 billion Swiss francs, as it carried out its strategic overhaul.

title: Manhattan rents hit an all-time high in January
description: Median rents in Manhattan hit a record in January, fueled by a strong job market and tight supply.

title: Singapore drops pre-departure requirements for travelers, further eases mask rules
description: Singapore is set to allow non-fully vaccinated travelers to enter the country without a negative pre-departure test from next week, health authorities announced Thursday.

title: Pressure on China’s factories grows as U.S. demand falls
description: All the factories that U.S. toy company Basic Fun works with in China told workers not to return right after the Lunar New Year holiday, said CEO Jay Foreman.
